description: Get the version of a table.

^(startingTimestamp)$.description:
The startingTimestamp of the query, a string in the  ISO8601 format, in the UTC timezone,
 such as 2022-01-01T00:00:00Z. the server needs to return the earliest table version at
 or after the provided timestamp, can be earlier than the timestamp of table version 0.

name.description: The table name to query. It's case-insensitive.

schema.description: The schema name to query. It's case-insensitive.

share.description: The share name to query. It's case-insensitive.
